RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 85. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 20 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Races Where Entered For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances ).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: METALLIC MAN raced up along the fence to take the lead shortly from the gate, set a pressured pace to the quarter pole, drew clear in upper stretch and finished willingly as much best. SHIPSHAPE broke alertly to be on top, was taken in hand to settle off the pace down the backside, made a steady gain from three wide midway on the turn to garner the place. BAREFOOTBOOTLEGGER stalked the pace from the fence in the second pair, rallied at the head of the lane cutting the corner and finished well to be up for the show. FLOWERPECKER pressed the pace to the top of the stretch and weakened through the lane. IDEA MAN slow early to be the trailer, rallied four wide in the turn to pass weaker rivals in the stretch. GUARD was one-paced and failed to menace. SACRED SKY tracked the pace in the second pair from two wide and lacked a response when called upon in the turn. SUDDEN SHIFT was never a threat.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 4 7 1/2F Turf CR: 73. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile on the main track. (Rail at 24 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIVI ME DREAMING raced three wide into the first turn angling in at the bend in front of RUN RUN RABBIT, continued to press the pace to the far turn from two wide, took command into the final bend, opened up turning for home and finished in a determined drive. LEUCADIA stalked the pace from the rail down the backside and made steady gains down the lane to be second. MARGARET'S LADY broke alertly to take command from the gate, raced five wide down the lane the first time, dropped to the rail into the turn, set the pace to midway on the final bend and kept on down the lane to hold the show. ISLE OF HOPE bumped leaving the gate and bobbled as a result, raced up mid-pack into the first turn, checked severely in traffic entering the first turn when impeded by RUN RUN RABBIT and bumping NATIVITY to his inside, was gathered up to level off, tracked mid-pack down the backside and made a mild late rally to hit the board in the stretch. RUN RUN RABBIT raced three wide into the first turn, angled in severely when in tight quarters as LIVI ME DREAMING angled into the first bend, caused ISLE OF HOPE and NATIVITY to bump and check severely on the bend, raced on to stalk the pace down the backstretch and weakened coming home. BY HEART unhurried in the early going and rallied mildly without impact. VAI GATTINA slow early and passed weakened rivals late. NATIVITY raced up the lane the first time in the two path, was bumped and caused to check hard into the first turn in a chain reaction, was taken in hand while getting out in reaction to the interference, eventually dropped back in hand to be near the rear of the field and went evenly the rest of the way. CLEARLY COPPER reserved to be mid-pack down the backside from four wide, bolted in the final bend to be taken in hand along the outside fence and eased to the wire. THE STEWARDS POSTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE ACTIONS ON THE FIRST TURN AND THE RIDER OF NATIVITY FILED AN OBJECTION AGAINST THE WINNER, UPON REVIEW THE STEWARDS DETERMINED THAT THE WINNER CROSSED INTO THE PATH OF SEVERAL RIVALS BY INTERFERING WITH RUN RUN RABBIT IN THE FIRST TURN.

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, steady gain, second best

ENTRY.COMMENT: checked hard, bumped, taken up, settled, no response

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 6 1M Turf CR: 73. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIMPLY JACK stalked the pace from the fence to the far turn, angled out turning for home to threaten, worked around the stopping pacesetter in upper stretch, angled back inside to engage the leader in mid-stretch and finished determinedly up the inside in a well handled ride. ACTION SEEKER pressed the pace from three wide through the final bend, assumed command at the top of the stretch and was out-finished late in the lane. STEP ON IT slow early to be at the rear of the field, made steady gains down the backside, circled six wide coming home and closed well to be gaining late. GHOST BIKE tracked three wide down the backside, mounted a rally midway on the turn to threaten at the head of the lane and finished evenly. BIG STORMY unhurried early to be near the rear of the field and made a late rally in the stretch. BOLD BALI well placed in mid-pack between rivals and failed to mount a rally. URSO GRAYDAR went evenly lacking a response when called upon. FIRE BRYAN set a pressured pace through the far turn and weakened late in the lane. ELECTRIC CHARGE was never a threat. CADE'S GOAL trailed most of the way and passed weaker in the stretch. WOODYTHEBIDSPOTTER pressed the pace to the far turn and stopped. JAKES CHANNEL raced mid-field for a half mile and came up empty.
